Date:  15/7/1940
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  9
Edition:
Quote:  There are two main types of fernlands in New Zealand - natural fernland, that is, land that carried fern before the first Europeans landed in the country, and artificially-induced fernland, or land which became covered in fern after the destruction of the forest .. Certain parts of Banks Peninsula are natural fernlands which have been in fern for a considerable period.
